ECHO(1)                        User Commands                        ECHO(1)

NAME
    echo - display a line of text

SYNOPSIS
    echo [OPTION]... [STRING]...

DESCRIPTION
    Print the STRINGs to standard output, separated by single spaces and
    followed by a newline.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils echo(1), ported to Horus and run as
    a ring-3 program from /bin/echo. It shadows the shell's own echo builtin
    when present.

OPTIONS
    -n    do not output the trailing newline
    -e    interpret backslash escapes (\n \t \\ \0NNN \xHH ...)
    -E    do not interpret backslash escapes (default)

    Run `echo --help` for the full option list.

NOTES
    The shell's redirection (echo TEXT > FILE) is handled by the shell's own
    echo builtin. Because /bin/echo shadows that builtin, redirection is not
    available when /bin/echo is installed; use the fss_create / fss_write
    builtins to write a file directly.

SEE ALSO
    printf(1), cat(1), hier(7)
